{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"278c462a-e89d-4972-a166-2817f09f3210","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_LBKx1GlRqhhgb8gw37W6em","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-c805078c17fa4a478d889ad6ad3304fd/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-c805078c17fa4a478d889ad6ad3304fd/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"f32183fa-6085-425a-89da-411a548dd7f3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` must come first.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":417,"requestId":"5C29:7D36C:60B6CB2:697FCC2:69F15603"},"id":"966826b6-b8de-4a4c-bd83-9ba2e8f58b53","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:51:28.889Z","parentId":"552efc16-0872-450f-b1e2-37adc7bf7244"}
